===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Originally an {{Han compound|壴|玨|ls=ic|t1=drum|t2=strings of jade|nocap=1}} – ceremony. Original form of {{zh-l|*禮}}.

In some bronze inscriptions, {{zh-l|*壴}} has been split into two, with {{zh-l|*豆}} on the bottom. Later scripts, including the seal script, have inherited this corruption, leading ''{{w|Shuowen}}'' to interpret this character as a {{liushu|p|nocap=1}} containing {{zh-l|*豆|vessel}}.

Due to similarity with the unrelated {{zh-l|*豐}}, 豊 has also been used as one of its variants.

